# Project Ready for Deployment: Style Redesign, Code Cleanup, & Database Stabilization

Removed all glassmorphism panel styling across the game application tabs, replacing it with the wood panel design system (matching the home center-panel) and adding corner screws to every panel. Added high-contrast color scheme overrides for visibility. Configured the game viewport layout to support zoom and scroll naturally. Fully documented the HTML structure with code block comments. Resolved database save race conditions. Cleaned up unused files.

## Changes Made

### 1. Deployment Cleanup (Unused Files Removed)
- [skribbl.io/](file:///c:/Users/PK'S/OneDrive/Desktop/AdvScribblw-with-backend-main/skribbl.io) [DELETED]
  - Recursively deleted the legacy `skribbl.io/` backup directory to reduce deployment footprint, saving over 2MB of project storage space (which contained raw offline PNG screenshots and duplicates of the frontend package assets).

### 2. Database Race Condition & Persistence Fix (`db.js`)
- [db.js](file:///c:/Users/PK'S/OneDrive/Desktop/AdvScribblw-with-backend-main/backend/db.js)
  - Replaced the asynchronous promise-write queue design with fully synchronous and atomic database reads (`readJSON`) and writes (`writeJSON`).
  - By performing these file modifications synchronously on Node's single thread, transaction interleaving is completely eliminated, ensuring concurrent registrations or payment updates never corrupt the JSON or overwrite each other.
  - Additionally, setting JSON queries to read dynamically from the disk on every action ensures manual edits to `users_db.json` (such as setting premium flags manually) are picked up immediately by the active dev server.

